===Etymology===
From {{etyl|enm}} {{term|shoo|lang=enm}}, from {{etyl|ang}} {{term|scoh|scōh|shoe|lang=ang}}, from {{etyl|gem-pro|en}} {{recons|skōhaz||shoe", literally "covering|lang=gem-pro}} (cf. Scots {{term|shae|lang=sco}}, West Frisian {{term|skoech|lang=fy}}, Dutch {{term|schoen|lang=nl}}, German {{term|Schuh|lang=de}}, Swedish {{term|sko|lang=sv}}), from {{etyl|ine-pro|en}} {{recons|skeuk-|lang=ine-pro}} (cf. Tocharian B {{term|skak|skāk|lang=txb}} ‘balcony’), from {{recons|(s)keu-||to cover|lang=ine-pro}}. More at {{l|en|sky}}.

